Source: Tarikh-I-Mubarak Shah by Yahya bin Ahmad Sirhindi via jayant20.
The Delhi sultanate rulers were well known for their oppressive policies towards the local Hindus. From jizya, to destruction of temples, Hindus of India had to go through a dark period during the regime of the five dynasties that ruled from Delhi and are collectively referred to as the &ldquo;Delhi Sultanate.&rdquo;
This was during the reign of Mubarak Shah, the second ruler of the dynasty.
